text:
winterlicious, 2015

for $25 pp, you get quite a lot of food. pate/salad was a nice app, lamb shank was very soft and fabulous. steak was a bit on the chewy side, and has lots of oily fatty parts - not my favorite. the desserts both were quite good also (chocolate and the creme brulee) 

cute place. friendly people. nice ambiance. I would probably return and try other things on the menu. well done.
